title: Grateful Dead Live at Oakland-Alameda County Coliseum on 1991-10-31
description:
Set 1

Help On The Way-> Slipknot!-> Franklin's Tower, Little Red Rooster, Loser, Just Like Tom Thumb's Blues, Let It Grow

Set 2

Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain, Truckin'-> Spoonful*, Dark Star*, Drums-> Jam**-> Dark Star*-> The Last Time*, Standing On the Moon-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away, E: Werewolves of London*

* with Gary Duncan, guitar. ** w/ Ken Kesey rap. Final / last Werewolves.

reviews.review_text:
Amazing mix, amazing night, a keeper This is one of the best MTX mixdowns available.  The show is delivered by a rested, energetic band with all players at the peak of their skills.  The sound quality is simply peerless.
Another treat is Gary Duncan (of Quicksilver Messenger Service) plays on half the songs in the second set - fitting in very well.
Played on a computer with sufficient speakerage, or piped to a bigger audio system (in my case a Sony 5 channel with 64-bit Digital DTS w/BOSE and JBL studio monitors) this is one of the most technically excellent recordings I have heard.
What I would give for a FLAC of the MTX master!  But the MP3 provides great listening pleasure.
A definite "must add" to your collection.
Truly Astonishing What can anyone say?
